<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sánchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo, 2020" authorityName="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Martínez &amp; Bonaldo" authorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Nopsma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nopsma leticia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leticia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Nopsma leticia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sánchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo, 2020" authorityName="Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Nopsma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nopsma florencia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florencia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Nopsma florencia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a similarly shaped membranous keel on embolus tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Drawings of male copulatory bulbs of Colombian Nopsma species. A, B. Nopsma florencia Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo. C, D. Nopsma macagual sp. nov. E, F. Nopsma leticia sp. nov. G, H. Nopsma paya sp. nov. A, C, E, G. Retrolateral view. B, D, F, H. Prolateral view. Scale bars: 0.7 mm. Abbreviations: e = embolus, mk = membranous keel, t = tegulum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566385" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">6A, B, E, F</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by having a larger tegulum, one-third of the cymbium length (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Nopsma leticia sp. nov., male (MPUJ-ENT 0070411). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566381" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">2C, D</figureCitation>
), and by the thicker embolus and membranous keel (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Drawings of male copulatory bulbs of Colombian Nopsma species. A, B. Nopsma florencia Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo. C, D. Nopsma macagual sp. nov. E, F. Nopsma leticia sp. nov. G, H. Nopsma paya sp. nov. A, C, E, G. Retrolateral view. B, D, F, H. Prolateral view. Scale bars: 0.7 mm. Abbreviations: e = embolus, mk = membranous keel, t = tegulum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566385" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">6E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Male</emphasis>
(holotype): Total length 3.92. Carapace 1.67 long, 1.42 wide. Sternum 1.02 long, 0.92 wide. Leg measurements: I: 4.37; II: 4.54; III: 4.31; IV: 5.52. Carapace orange-brown with remarkable dorsal pattern of dark brown stains (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Nopsma leticia sp. nov., male (MPUJ-ENT 0070411). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566381" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">2A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae, palps, sternum, endites, labium and legs orangish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Nopsma leticia sp. nov., male (MPUJ-ENT 0070411). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566381" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">2B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen dorsally gray with tenuous light stripes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Nopsma leticia sp. nov., male (MPUJ-ENT 0070411). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566381" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">2A</figureCitation>
), ventrally yellowish (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Nopsma leticia sp. nov., male (MPUJ-ENT 0070411). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566381" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">2B</figureCitation>
). Anal tubercle and spinnerets pale yellowish. Palp with rounded tegulum and a posteriorly directed embolus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Nopsma leticia sp. nov., male (MPUJ-ENT 0070411). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566381" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">2C, D</figureCitation>
), with a long membranous keel, reaching more than one-third of the embolus tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Drawings of male copulatory bulbs of Colombian Nopsma species. A, B. Nopsma florencia Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo. C, D. Nopsma macagual sp. nov. E, F. Nopsma leticia sp. nov. G, H. Nopsma paya sp. nov. A, C, E, G. Retrolateral view. B, D, F, H. Prolateral view. Scale bars: 0.7 mm. Abbreviations: e = embolus, mk = membranous keel, t = tegulum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566385" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">6F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Female</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">The specific name is a noun in apposition taken from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="variation">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Males (n=5): total length: 2.68-3.99; carapace length: 1.54-1.71.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">
Known from two localities in Amazonas department (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Distribution map of Colombian Nopsma species. Nopsma florencia Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo (circle), Nopsma leticia sp. nov. (triangles), Nopsma macagual sp. nov. (star) and Nopsma paya sp. nov. (polygon)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566387" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
